## TASK: Convert React Frontend → Laravel Blade (Full Stack)

### PROJECT CONTEXT
This is "Skoolyst Social AI" — a Social Media Management SaaS.
Currently: React (Vite + TypeScript + TailwindCSS) frontend + Laravel API backend (separate).
Goal: Eliminate React entirely. Rebuild the entire UI as Laravel Blade views served by Laravel web routes, using the same TailwindCSS classes already in the React components.

### CURRENT REACT PAGES TO CONVERT (1:1 mapping)
Each React page/component → equivalent Blade view:

| React File                          | Laravel Route & Blade View                     |
|-------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| LoginPage.tsx                       | GET /login → auth/login.blade.php              |
| RegisterPage.tsx                    | GET /register → auth/register.blade.php        |
| DashboardPage.tsx                   | GET /dashboard → dashboard.blade.php           |
| CreatePostPage.tsx                  | GET /create → posts/create.blade.php           |
| PostsPage.tsx                       | GET /posts → posts/index.blade.php             |
| ScheduledPostsPage.tsx              | GET /scheduled → posts/scheduled.blade.php     |
| AccountsPage.tsx                    | GET /accounts → accounts/index.blade.php       |
| AnalyticsPage.tsx                   | GET /analytics → analytics/index.blade.php     |
| SettingsPage.tsx                    | GET /settings → settings/index.blade.php       |
| ProfilePage.tsx                     | GET /profile → profile/index.blade.php         |
| SwitchAccountPage.tsx               | GET /switch-account → workspaces/switch.blade.php |
| NotificationsPage.tsx               | GET /notifications → notifications/index.blade.php |
| ActivityPage.tsx                    | GET /activity → activity/index.blade.php       |
| Sidebar.tsx                         | components/sidebar.blade.php                   |
| TopBar.tsx                          | components/topbar.blade.php                    |
| StatCard.tsx                        | components/stat-card.blade.php                 |
| Toast/ToastContainer.tsx            | components/toast.blade.php (Alpine.js)         |
| PostComposer.tsx                    | components/post-composer.blade.php             |
| RevenueChart.tsx                    | components/revenue-chart.blade.php (Chart.js)  |

### EXISTING BACKEND (DO NOT CHANGE API ROUTES)
These Laravel API routes already exist and work. Keep them exactly as-is:
- POST /api/login, /api/register, /api/logout
- GET /api/user, PUT /api/user/profile, PUT /api/user/password
- GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE /api/workspaces/{workspace}/posts
- GET /api/workspaces/{workspace}/social-accounts
- GET /api/workspaces/{workspace}/social-platforms
- POST /api/workspaces/{workspace}/social-platforms/{slug}/connect
- POST /api/posts/publish
- GET /api/auth/facebook/redirect, /api/auth/facebook/callback

### TECH STACK FOR BLADE CONVERSION
- TailwindCSS (same classes from React — copy them directly)
- Alpine.js (replaces React state/hooks — for dropdowns, modals, toggles)
- Laravel Livewire (optional, only for highly interactive components like PostComposer and PostsPage filters)
- Axios or fetch() via <script> tags for AJAX calls that still need API (e.g. publish post)
- Chart.js via CDN for RevenueChart
- Vite (already configured in Laravel) for CSS/JS bundling
- Laravel Sanctum for session-based auth (switch from token to cookie/session auth)

### ARCHITECTURE RULES (from .cursorrules)
- Controllers: HTTP only — validate, call service, return view. NO business logic.
- Services: All business logic (already exists: SocialPostService, SocialAccountProvisioner).
- FormRequests: All validation (already exists: StorePostRequest).
- Blade Components: Build <x-button>, <x-card>, <x-alert>, <x-input>, <x-badge>, <x-modal>, <x-stat-card>, <x-sidebar>, <x-topbar>, <x-page-header>. Use them EVERYWHERE — no raw HTML buttons or cards in page views.
- Models: Already exist (Post, SocialAccount, Workspace, User, etc.) — do not modify.

