### AUTH CHANGE (important)
React used Bearer tokens (localStorage). Laravel Blade will use:
- `Auth::attempt()` for login → session-based
- `@auth` / `@guest` directives for route protection
- Middleware `auth` on all protected web routes
- Keep API routes as-is for any remaining AJAX needs

### COPY UI EXACTLY
- Copy TailwindCSS class names from React TSX files directly into Blade.
- Colors, spacing, grid layouts, responsive breakpoints — replicate exactly.
- Sidebar collapsed state → Alpine.js `x-data="{ collapsed: false }"`.
- Toast notifications → Alpine.js with `x-show` and auto-dismiss timer.
- Modals → Alpine.js `x-data="{ open: false }"`.

### WHAT TO BUILD FIRST (priority order)
1. layouts/app.blade.php + components/sidebar + components/topbar
2. auth/login + auth/register + AuthController (web, session-based)
3. dashboard.blade.php + DashboardController
4. posts/create.blade.php + PostComposer component
5. posts/index + posts/scheduled
6. accounts/index
7. Remaining pages (analytics, settings, profile, notifications, activity)

### DO NOT
- Do not create new API endpoints. Existing ones are fine.
- Do not modify existing Models, Migrations, or Services.
- Do not use React, Vue, or any JS framework — Alpine.js only.
- Do not inline business logic in controllers.
- Do not use `$request->validate()` inline — use FormRequests.